    <br />
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-8">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <h3>
                            Custom Commands<br/><small>Reuse all the things!</small>
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>
                        Command modules are decoupled from the service they run in, giving you more control over which tasks can be executed in each service.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <h3>
                            Optional Request and Response Serialization<br/><small>Occam's Razor never felt so good!</small>
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>
                        Optimize your commands by sidestepping serialization. If your command accepts a simple string, don't give it an entire XML or JSON wrapper. Just give it the string.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <h3>
                            Unprecedented Trace Logging<br /><small>Keep your friends close and your logger closer.</small>
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>
                        &lt;More Stuff Here&gt;
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <h3>
                            Free NuGet Packages<br /><small>Build it fast! Build it right!</small>
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>
                        Hit the ground running with rapid SOA development right here, right now.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-4">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <h3>
                            Why HyperSOA?
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>
                        The HyperSOA Framework picks up where WCF left off. The framework provides a fully functional, fully customizable server-side component that accept commands completely defined by you.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
